      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TAW MAJOR (2) boasts a strong record this course with 11 wins and eight minors from 26 tries. Below best last time at this track (30.08) in a NG, finishing a 8 length fifth. Looks suited and should go close. GOLD FORCE (3) boasts a strong record this journey here with three wins and two minors from seven tries. Was out of the placings last time (29.79) at this track in a NG, finishing sixth and beaten 6 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. WEST ROCK CASEY (1) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 29.80 beating President Rolex. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Should be in this for a long way. FOREIGN CAPITAL (5) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
